  "body": "When a repo is removed, using the \"helm repo remove\" command, it leaves behind a cache of the repo's index.yaml file in \"~/.helm/repository/cache/\"\nAfterwards, performing a helm search, will still display charts from the removed repo...\n### Steps to reproduce:\n\n`$ helm repo add kubernetes-charts http://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-charts`\n`$ helm search alpine`\n`kubernetes-charts/alpine-0.1.0.tgz`\n`$ $  ls ~/.helm/repository/cache/kubernetes-charts*`\n`/home/user/.helm/repository/cache/kubernetes-charts-index.yaml`\n`$ helm repo remove kubernetes-charts`\n`$ helm search alpine`\n`kubernetes-charts/alpine-0.1.0.tgz`\n`$ $  ls ~/.helm/repository/cache/kubernetes-charts*`\n`/home/user/.helm/repository/cache/kubernetes-charts-index.yaml`\n### Expected:\n\n\"helm remove repo\" should clear the repo's index cache.\n\"helm search\" should not display charts from removed repos.\n",
